"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe autonomic nervous system is divided into the sympathetic and parasympathetic systems. The sympathetic fibres originate from the thoracolumbar region of the spinal cord, specifically from \u003Cstrong\u003ET1 to L2\u003C/strong\u003E. These fibres are responsible for the \u0027fight or flight\u0027 response.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe parasympathetic fibres originate from the craniosacral region, specifically from \u003Cstrong\u003ES2 to S4\u003C/strong\u003E. These fibres are responsible for the \u0027rest and digest\u0027 functions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETherefore, the spinal segments that encompass all segments with autonomic fibres in their anterior roots are \u003Cstrong\u003ET1-L2, S2-4\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Autonomic fibres in spinal nerves are part of the sympathetic and parasympathetic nervous systems.","Sympathetic fibres originate from the thoracolumbar region, specifically T1 to L2.","Parasympathetic fibres originate from the craniosacral region, specifically S2 to S4."],"references":["Kaiser JT, Lugo-Pico JG. Neuroanatomy, Spinal Nerves. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK542218/","Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons.","Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022).\u00a0The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55144"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17279"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55144","links":{"self